Anyone who has registered to ride a school bus for the 2020-2021 school year should pick up their child‚Äôs bus fob in the front of the high school from 4-7pm today if you have not already picked up.

Fobs will also be available at the Transportation Office (601 Railroad Ave) Wednesday from 6:00 am - 4:00 pm. If you can not make it during these times, we will have them at your child's respective building the first day of school.

The transportation department is asking parents contact them if their students transportation needs have changed from what was initially registered (whether they now need transportation or no longer need it). Also contact the Transportation Dept to set up shuttle services this year (so they can designate and assign buses for these purposes). Key fobs will be issued for all riders. You may contact them at 527-4116.

post_text:
All of our performers at this year‚Äôs Virtual State Speech Contest did a fantastic job! The Glenwood Speech team earned overall 1 ratings in ALL 6 performances. We want to especially recognize seniors Audrey Arnold and Cody Lampman, for their All State Nominations. Although there is no festival to perform at this year, they are being honored and recognized as if they were. Less than 5% of all performers who start the Individual Speech Season at District Contest are honored each year as All State Performers.

The entire Individual Speech Team worked really hard this year, learned a lot, accepted the challenges of new categories and of performing virtually, and we couldn't be more proud! Looking forward to another successful season next year!

post_text: There seems to be confusion on the Governor's update today regarding school days. If schools do not choose one of the options for continuous learning, April 13 - April 30 must be made up. Schools have until April 10 to inform the state of their intentions. We plan to do that so April 13 - April 30 will not need to be made up. We hope this clarifies the confusion. Additionally, we are in a mode of continuous learning right now. It just needs to be formalized and we need to decide whether or not we will have it be required at some level. This means that regardless of our decison, we WILL be having remote continuous learning going on through April 30. Our return date to school is now May 1, 2020.

The Opinion-Tribune
April 2 at 4:39 PM ¬∑

GCHS SENIORS and PARENTS. We need your help! We don't want you or your Glenwood Community High School senior to get left out of our annual GCHS graduation section scheduled to be published next month. There is NO CHARGE for having your senior's photo and profile published in this keepsake special section. The easiest and safest way to submit your photo and profile is by e-mailing the photo and the information we need to composition@opinion-tribune.com. The information we're requesting for the profile is on the form attached to this post. You may also print off the form, fill it out, attach your photo and stick it in our mail slot right next to the front door of our office at 116 S. Walnut St. (north of fire station). If you bring the form/photo to our office, please put it in an envelope and write the graduate's name on the back of photo. Please call 527-3191 if you have any questions. Thank you.

post_text:
Let's Celebrate!! Celebrate our students, teachers, administration and the community that comes together to make sure we have the support to succeed, even during the most trying times. We will never forget the challenges of 2019 yet West Elementary weathered the adversity and made it happen!

Scoring in the top 15% of Iowa Schools, West Elementary received the designation of a High Performing School on their Iowa Statewide Assessment. TOP 15%!!!!! That's as huge as the donuts students received. And that's pretty huge!

When asked how many think we have what it takes to do as well or better next year, these are the hands that flew up. We think they are well on their way! Congratulations West Elementary and thanks for all you do to give our students a great education.

post_text:
Preschool Prescreening -

Northeast Early Childhood Center (NECC) will be hosting its annual Preschool Prescreening event on March 19th and 20th, 2020. If you are interested in your child attending preschool at NECC for the 2020-2021 school year, please contact them right away at 712-527-4875 to be placed on the mailing list and to receive additional information about the upcoming prescreening event. In order for your child to be eligible to attend preschool next year, they must be at least 3 years of age on or before 09-15-2020.

Glenwood will not compete in the competition for a place as for being the host school but will be judged & perform at 8:20pm.

The cost of admission is $15 for adults and $10 for kids which allows you to come and go all day. Proceeds go to support this talented group of artists.
